Here's an example Python function that uses the pandas library to read data from an Excel spreadsheet:
```python
import pandas as pd

def read_excel(file_path):
    df = pd.read_excel(file_path)
    return df
```
This function takes a file path as input and returns a Pandas DataFrame that contains the data from the Excel spreadsheet. You can use this function to read data from any Excel file on your computer by passing the file path as an argument. For example:
```python
df = read_excel('path/to/my/file.xlsx')
print(df)
```
This will print the contents of the Excel spreadsheet in a Pandas DataFrame format.
Note that you'll need to have pandas installed on your system in order to use this function. You can install pandas using pip:
```bash
pip install pandas
```
